      "block_type": "heading-sub",
      "text": "Liquidation activities",
      "table_content": null,
      "hyperlinks": [],
      "children": [
        {
          "block_type": "paragraph-1",
          "text": "The mandate of the United Nations Investigative Team to Promote Accountability for Crimes Committed by Da’esh/Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant (UNITAD) was defined in Security Council resolution 2379 (2017) and extended in subsequent resolutions of the Council. In its resolution 2697 (2023), the Council, at the request of the Government of Iraq, decided to extend the mandate of UNITAD until 17 September 2024 only.",
          "table_content": null,
          "hyperlinks": [],
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "block_type": "paragraph-1",
          "text": "The administrative liquidation of UNITAD, including the disposal of assets, was carried out from 18 September to 31 December 2024, and was facilitated by UNAMI.",
          "table_content": null,
          "hyperlinks": [],
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "block_type": "paragraph-1",
          "text": "The General Assembly, by its resolution 78/253, appropriated the amount of $25.7 million for 2024.  UNITAD incurred $20.0 million in expenditure for the period, representing a resource utilization rate of 78 per cent, as result of the closure of the mission in September while provision was made in the budget for a 12-month period.",
          "table_content": null,
          "hyperlinks": [],
          "children": []
        },
